@page "/blog/small-business-money-tips"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@inherits BlogPostBase

<PageTitle>SmartBudget - Small Business Money Tips</PageTitle>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/blog.css" />

<div class="blog-post-page">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="breadcrumb-container">
            <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house-door"></i> Home</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/blog">Blog</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">Small Business Money Tips</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
        </div>

        <article class="blog-post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <span class="post-category-badge">Business</span>
                <h1>Money Management Tips for Small Business Owners</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span><i class="bi bi-person-circle"></i> Emeka Okafor</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-calendar3"></i> @CurrentDate</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-clock"></i> 7 min read</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="post-body-content">
                <p>Managing business finances is crucial for success. These money management tips will help you grow your small business in @CurrentYear.</p>

                <h2>1. Separate Business and Personal Finances</h2>
                <p>Open a dedicated business bank account. This makes tracking business expenses easier and helps with tax filing.</p>

                <h2>2. Track Every Expense</h2>
                <p>Use SmartBudget to track all business expenses. Know where your money is going.</p>

                <h2>3. Create a Business Budget</h2>
                <p>Plan your business expenses and income. A budget helps you make informed decisions.</p>

                <h2>4. Build an Emergency Fund for Your Business</h2>
                <p>Save 3-6 months of operating expenses for unexpected challenges.</p>

                <h2>5. Understand Your Business Cash Flow</h2>
                <p>Monitor when money comes in and goes out. This helps you plan for slow periods.</p>

                <h2>6. Keep Business and Personal Taxes Separate</h2>
                <p>Set aside money for taxes throughout the year. This prevents surprises during tax season.</p>

                <h2>7. Use SmartBudget for Business</h2>
                <p>Track business expenses, create budgets, and monitor your financial health.</p>

                <h2>8. Review Your Finances Regularly</h2>
                <p>Set aside time each week or month to review your business finances.</p>

                <div class="post-cta">
                    <h3>Grow Your Business</h3>
                    <p>Use SmartBudget to manage your business finances effectively.</p>
                    <a href="/Account/Register" class="btn-cta">Get Started Free →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</div>


@code {
    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        PageName = "blog-post";
        await base.OnInitializedAsync();
    }
}